1911-22 Browning Black Label Compact
 
Mdl: 051815490      3.625” Barrel     MSRP: $639.99 NIB SALE PRICE $499.99
 
Browning’s 1911-22 has made .22 popular again. This high strength, light weight, A1 style compact is constructed with a polymer frame design and was originally introduced in 2011. Gun reviews have been favorable attesting to the design and construction holding up well. Weighs under a pound when loaded and fits both large and small hands while still retaining the safety and “manual of arms” of the original John Browning 1911 full size with blowback slide action and single-action trigger.
 
Standard features include stainless steel barrel block, target crown, machined aluminum slide, fixed sights, steel 10 round magazine, manual thumb and grip safeties. But this gun comes in a compact 6.5” length overall which is approximately 85% the size of a full size 1911.
 
The “Black Label” models have enhanced features such as laminated and stippled grips with checkered front strap, matte black finish, extended ambidextrous thumb safety, Beavertail grip safety, Commander style hammer and extended slide release.
 
At the most recent Wichita area gun show there was only one 1911-22 and that wasn’t a close match to this gun as it was a used, earlier specimen with the first generation “flat” black finish selling for $525 without the case and paperwork.
